Class CoarseToFineMaxRuleParser

All Implemented Interfaces:

Direct Known Subclasses:
CoarseToFineNBestParser, CoarseToFineTwoChartsParser
public class CoarseToFineMaxRuleParser
extends ConstrainedArrayParser

Author:
Slav Petrov SHOULD BE CLEANED UP!!! AND PROBABLY ALSO RENAMED SINCE IT CAN COMPUTE VITERBI PARSES AS WELL An extension of ConstrainedArrayParser that computes the scores P(w_{i:j}|A), whose computation involves a sum, rather than the Viterbi scores, which involve a max. This is used by the Labelled Recall parser (maximizes the expected number of correct symbols) and the Max-Rule parser (maximizes the expected number of correct rules, ie all 3 symbols correct).
